## Step 2: Analyze the binary protections

```
level01@OverRide:~$ readelf -l ./level01 | grep GNU_STACK
  GNU_STACK      0x000000 0x00000000 0x00000000 0x00000 0x00000 RWE 0x4
```

| Protection | Status | Impact |
|-----------|--------|--------|
| **Canary** | Disabled | No stack overflow detection |
| **NX** | Disabled (RWE) | Stack is executable â€” shellcode possible, but ret2libc is simpler |
| **PIE** | Disabled | Fixed addresses |
| **RELRO** | Partial | GOT is writable (not needed for this exploit) |

